{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":680,"text":"For over a decade,"},{"time":2680,"text":"I have studied young people\nthat have been pushed out of school,"},{"time":7760,"text":"so called \"dropouts.\""},{"time":10320,"text":"As they end up failed\nby the education system,"},{"time":13800,"text":"they're on the streets\nwhere they're vulnerable to violence,"},{"time":17360,"text":"police harassment,"},{"time":18840,"text":"police brutality"},{"time":20320,"text":"and incarceration."},{"time":22600,"text":"I follow these young people\nfor years at a time,"},{"time":26800,"text":"across institutional settings,"},{"time":29240,"text":"to try to understand what some of us call\nthe \"school-to-prison pipeline.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":36720,"text":"When you look at a picture like this,"},{"time":38720,"text":"of young people who are in my study ..."},{"time":43440,"text":"you might see trouble."},{"time":44880,"text":"I mean one of the boys\nhas a bottle of liquor in his hand,"},{"time":49080,"text":"he's 14 years old"},{"time":51240,"text":"and it's a school day."},{"time":53440,"text":"Other people, when they see this picture,"},{"time":55960,"text":"might see gangs,"},{"time":58000,"text":"thugs, delinquents --"},{"time":60120,"text":"criminals."},{"time":61680,"text":"But I see it different."},{"time":64000,"text":"I see these young people\nthrough a perspective"},{"time":67520,"text":"that looks at the assets\nthat they bring to the education system."},{"time":72320,"text":"So will you join me in changing\nthe way we label young people"},{"time":77360,"text":"from \"at-risk\" to \"at-promise?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":82480,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":89800,"text":"How do I know that these young people"},{"time":91640,"text":"have the potential\nand the promise to change?"},{"time":95120,"text":"I know this because I am one of them."},{"time":98680,"text":"You see, I grew up\nin dire poverty in the inner city,"},{"time":103040,"text":"without a father --"},{"time":104280,"text":"he abandoned me before I was even born."},{"time":107280,"text":"We were on welfare,"},{"time":109120,"text":"sometimes homeless,"},{"time":110440,"text":"many times hungry."},{"time":112720,"text":"By the time I was 15 years old,"},{"time":115040,"text":"I had been incarcerated in juvy\nthree times for three felonies."},{"time":120240,"text":"My best friend had already been killed."},{"time":123760,"text":"And soon after,"},{"time":125280,"text":"while I'm standing next to my uncle,"},{"time":127840,"text":"he gets shot."},{"time":129560,"text":"And as I'm waiting\nfor the ambulance to arrive"},{"time":132080,"text":"for over an hour ..."},{"time":136000,"text":"he bleeds to death on the street."},{"time":140600,"text":"I had lost faith and hope in the world,"},{"time":144360,"text":"and I had given up on the system\nbecause the system had failed me."},{"time":148520,"text":"I had nothing to offer"},{"time":150640,"text":"and no one had anything to offer me."},{"time":155160,"text":"I was fatalistic."},{"time":156760,"text":"I didn't even think\nI could make it to my 18th birthday."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160440,"text":"The reason I'm here today"},{"time":162680,"text":"is because a teacher\nthat cared reached out"},{"time":167200,"text":"and managed to tap into my soul."},{"time":171000,"text":"This teacher,"},{"time":172400,"text":"Ms. Russ ..."},{"time":175920,"text":"she was the kind of teacher\nthat was always in your business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180240,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":182000,"text":"She was the kind of teacher that was like,"},{"time":184480,"text":"\"Victor, I'm here for you\nwhenever you're ready.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":187640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":189880,"text":"I wasn't ready."},{"time":191560,"text":"But she understood one basic principle\nabout young people like me."},{"time":195840,"text":"We're like oysters."},{"time":197760,"text":"We're only going to open up\nwhen we're ready,"},{"time":200520,"text":"and if you're not there when we're ready,"},{"time":203960,"text":"we're going to clam back up."},{"time":206400,"text":"Ms. Russ was there for me."},{"time":208120,"text":"She was culturally relevant,"},{"time":210160,"text":"she respected my community,\nmy people, my family."},{"time":214320,"text":"I told her a story about my Uncle Ruben."},{"time":218240,"text":"He would take me to work with him\nbecause I was broke,"},{"time":220920,"text":"and he knew I needed some money."},{"time":222800,"text":"He collected glass bottles for a living."},{"time":226640,"text":"Four in the morning on a school day,"},{"time":228400,"text":"we'd throw the glass bottles\nin the back of his van,"},{"time":231760,"text":"and the bottles would break."},{"time":233760,"text":"And my hands and arms would start to bleed"},{"time":235840,"text":"and my tennis shoes and pants\nwould get all bloody."},{"time":240320,"text":"And I was terrified and in pain,\nand I would stop working."},{"time":244880,"text":"And my uncle, he would look me in the eyes\nand he would say to me,"},{"time":248200,"text":"\"Mijo,"},{"time":249560,"text":"estamos buscando vida.\""},{"time":253040,"text":"\"We're searching for a better life,"},{"time":255600,"text":"we're trying to make\nsomething out of nothing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":260880,"text":"Ms. Russ listened to my story,"},{"time":263720,"text":"welcomed it into the classroom and said,"},{"time":266240,"text":"\"Victor, this is your power."},{"time":268920,"text":"This is your potential."},{"time":270840,"text":"Your family, your culture, your community\nhave taught you a hard-work ethic"},{"time":276160,"text":"and you will use it to empower\nyourself in the academic world"},{"time":281520,"text":"so you can come back\nand empower your community.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":286520,"text":"With Ms. Russ's help,"},{"time":288440,"text":"I ended up returning to school."},{"time":291480,"text":"I even finished my credits on time"},{"time":295480,"text":"and graduated with my class."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298160,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305760,"text":"But Ms. Russ said to me\nright before graduation,"},{"time":308440,"text":"\"Victor, I'm so proud of you."},{"time":311720,"text":"I knew you could do it."},{"time":313720,"text":"Now it's time to go to college.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":316960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":319320,"text":"College, me?"},{"time":320560,"text":"Man, what is this teacher smoking\nthinking I'm going to college?"},{"time":324480,"text":"I applied with the mentors\nand support she provided,"},{"time":328920,"text":"got a letter of acceptance,"},{"time":331040,"text":"and one of the paragraphs read,"},{"time":333280,"text":"\"You've been admitted\nunder probationary status.\""},{"time":337400,"text":"I said, \"Probation?\nI'm already on probation,"},{"time":339920,"text":"that don't matter?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":341160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":342440,"text":"It was academic probation,\nnot criminal probation."},{"time":347320,"text":"But what do teachers like Ms. Russ\ndo to succeed with young people"},{"time":351160,"text":"like the ones I study?"},{"time":353080,"text":"I propose three strategies."},{"time":355280,"text":"The first:"},{"time":356520,"text":"let's get rid of our\ndeficit perspective in education."},{"time":360720,"text":"\"These people\ncome from a culture of violence,"},{"time":363000,"text":"a culture of poverty."},{"time":364280,"text":"These people are at-risk;\nthese people are truant."},{"time":366880,"text":"These people are empty containers\nfor us to fill with knowledge."},{"time":373040,"text":"They have the problems,"},{"time":374720,"text":"we have the solutions.\""},{"time":378200,"text":"Number two."},{"time":379840,"text":"Let's value the stories that young people\nbring to the schoolhouse."},{"time":385560,"text":"Their stories of overcoming\ninsurmountable odds are so powerful."},{"time":391080,"text":"And I know you know some of these stories."},{"time":396840,"text":"These very same stories and experiences"},{"time":400120,"text":"already have grit, character\nand resilience in them."},{"time":405640,"text":"So let's help young people\nrefine those stories."},{"time":408840,"text":"Let's help them be proud of who they are,"},{"time":410840,"text":"because our education system\nwelcomes their families, their cultures,"},{"time":414800,"text":"their communities"},{"time":416040,"text":"and the skill set\nthey've learned to survive."},{"time":419680,"text":"And of course the third strategy\nbeing the most important:"},{"time":423840,"text":"resources."},{"time":425080,"text":"We have to provide\nadequate resources to young people."},{"time":430040,"text":"Grit alone isn't going to cut it."},{"time":434080,"text":"You can sit there\nand tell me all you want,"},{"time":436280,"text":"\"Hey man, pick yourself up\nby the bootstraps.\""},{"time":439440,"text":"But if I was born\nwithout any straps on my boots --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":442520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":443760,"text":"How am I supposed to pick myself up?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":445520,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":453520,"text":"Job training,"},{"time":454760,"text":"mentoring,"},{"time":456000,"text":"counseling ..."},{"time":457720,"text":"Teaching young people\nto learn from their mistakes"},{"time":460480,"text":"instead of criminalizing them,"},{"time":462200,"text":"and dragging them out\nof their classrooms like animals."},{"time":467400,"text":"How about this?"},{"time":468640,"text":"I propose that we implement restorative\njustice in every high school in America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474400,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":481200,"text":"So we went out to test these ideas\nin the community of Watts in LA"},{"time":487080,"text":"with 40 young people\nthat had been pushed out of school."},{"time":490360,"text":"William was one of them."},{"time":492600,"text":"William was the kind of kid\nthat had been given every label."},{"time":496920,"text":"He had dropped out, he was a gang member,"},{"time":500160,"text":"a criminal."},{"time":502200,"text":"And when we met him he was very resistant."},{"time":504800,"text":"But I remember what Ms. Russ used to say."},{"time":507240,"text":"\"Hey, I'm here for you\nwhenever you're ready.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":510560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512039,"text":"So over time --"},{"time":514480,"text":"over time he began to open up."},{"time":516720,"text":"And I remember the day\nthat he made the switch."},{"time":519960,"text":"We were in a large group"},{"time":521640,"text":"and a young lady in our program was crying"},{"time":524760,"text":"because she told us her powerful story"},{"time":528520,"text":"of her dad being killed"},{"time":531720,"text":"and then his body being shown\nin the newspaper the next day."},{"time":539960,"text":"And as she's crying,\nI don't know what to do,"},{"time":542200,"text":"so I give her her space,"},{"time":543960,"text":"and William had enough."},{"time":546640,"text":"He slammed his hands\non the desk and he said,"},{"time":549640,"text":"\"Hey, everybody! Group hug! Group hug!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":555640,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":563160,"text":"This young lady's tears and pain\nturned into joy and laughter"},{"time":569200,"text":"knowing that her community had her back,"},{"time":573800,"text":"and William had now learned\nthat he did have a purpose in life:"},{"time":578600,"text":"to help to heal the souls\nof people in his own community."},{"time":584520,"text":"He told us his story."},{"time":586200,"text":"We refined his story"},{"time":588000,"text":"to go from being the story of a victim\nto being the story of a survivor"},{"time":592840,"text":"that has overcome adversity."},{"time":595240,"text":"We placed high value on it."},{"time":597680,"text":"William went on to finish high school,"},{"time":602360,"text":"get his security guard certificate\nto become a security guard,"},{"time":607120,"text":"and is now working\nat a local school district."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":619760,"text":"Ms. Russ's mantra --"},{"time":621360,"text":"her mantra was always,"},{"time":623640,"text":"\"when you teach to the heart,\nthe mind will follow.\""},{"time":630600,"text":"The great writer Khalil Gibran says,"},{"time":635200,"text":"\"Out of suffering\nhave emerged the greatest souls."},{"time":640440,"text":"The massive characters\nare seared with scars.\""},{"time":646040,"text":"I believe that in this education\nrevolution that we're talking about"},{"time":651720,"text":"we need to invite the souls\nof the young people that we work with,"},{"time":656680,"text":"and once they're able to refine --"},{"time":658960,"text":"identify their grit,\nresilience and character"},{"time":662040,"text":"that they've already developed --"},{"time":665080,"text":"their academic performance will improve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671360,"text":"Let's believe in young people."},{"time":673720,"text":"Let's provide them\nthe right kinds of resources."},{"time":677040,"text":"I'll tell you what my teacher did for me."},{"time":679720,"text":"She believed in me so much"},{"time":683120,"text":"that she tricked me\ninto believing in myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687240,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688480,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}